config RTL8196E_UART_BRIDGE
	bool "Realtek RTL8196E in-kernel UART<->TCP bridge"
	depends on MIPS && SERIAL_8250 && INET
	help
	  In-kernel byte shoveler between a TTY port (typically /dev/ttyS1,
	  the link to the Silabs EFR32 Zigbee/Thread radio) and a listening
	  TCP socket. Replaces the userspace serialgateway daemon, removing
	  the user/kernel context-switch overhead per byte that capped the
	  earlier daemon at moderate baud rates on the single-core Lexra
	  RLX4181. Sustains 892857 baud (the SoC's N+1 divisor maximum) with
	  no overrun/framing errors under multi-hour soak.

	  Protocol-agnostic: forwards raw bytes in both directions, used by
	  EZSP (NCP), CPC (RCP), and Spinel (OT-RCP) clients alike.

	  Must be built in (=y), not as a module. The driver registers at
	  late_initcall and depends on the tty/serial and net subsystems
	  being initialized; there is no module exit path because the
	  driver is never unloaded.

	  If unsure, say N.
